question:
Find $M^2+(A^T\cdot B)^{-1}$, where $A=\left( \begin{array}{rrr}
-1 & 3 & 2 \end{array}
\right)$, $B=\left( \begin{array}{rrr}
-2 & 4 & 1 \end{array}
\right)$, and $M=\left( \begin{array}{rrr}
7 & 2 & 1 \\
-1 & 3 & 0  \\
2 & 0 & -2 \end{array}
\right)$.

Indicate which of the following is a linear combination of $A=\left[\begin{array}{rr}
      3& 2\\
			0 & 1 
    \end{array}\right]$, $B=\left[\begin{array}{rr}
      0& -1 \\
			1 & 2 
    \end{array}\right]$ and $C=\left[\begin{array}{rr}
      5& 4 \\
			-1 & 0
    \end{array}\right]$.

Indicate which of the following is a linear combination of $A=\left[\begin{array}{rr}
      3& 2\\
			0 & 1 
    \end{array}\right]$, $B=\left[\begin{array}{rr}
      0& -1 \\
			1 & 2 
    \end{array}\right]$ and $C=\left[\begin{array}{rr}
      5& 4 \\
			-1 & 0
    \end{array}\right]$.

